"{\"uid\": \"yellowhammernews.com-olympics-opening-ceremony-blatantly-mocks-christianity-in-bizarre-drag-queen-performance\", \"text\": \"Politics  Business  Faith & Culture  Sports  Radio  Menu  \\u00d7  Politics  Business  Faith & Culture  Sports  About Us  Team  Events  Radio Network  Politics  -  Share:  Twitter  LinkedIn  Facebook  The opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympics in Paris is igniting widespread outrage over drag-queen themed portrayals of religious and historical figures, including a unsettling parody of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\" painting, which depicts the last meal Jesus had with his apostles.  What have men in dresses mocking Christians at a fake last supper got to do with the Olympics?  Why has every European and US \\\"event\\\" become a predictable  platform to mainline minority fetishes into the lives of a bemused majority?  We are sick of it.pic.twitter.com/hQfuFaM1NW  - Chay Bowes (@BowesChay)July 26, 2024    Viewers quickly recognized the portrayal with drag queens as an intentional mockery of Christianity. Prominent figures likeElon Muskand U.S. Speaker of the HouseMike Johnson(R-LA) criticized the \\\"shocking and insulting\\\" performance sanctioned by the Olympics. U.S. Senator Katie Britt condemned it as a deliberate act to insult Christians.  \\\"This was an intentional choice to mock Christianity and Christians. It's disgraceful. And it's the same kind of bizarre craziness that's being pushed on children and teenagers across America. We need to turn our eyes back to God and restore common sense,\\\" Sen. Britt (R-Montgomery) wrote.  This was an intentional choice to mock Christianity and Christians.  It's disgraceful. And it's the same kind of bizarre craziness that's being pushed on children and teenagers across America. We need to turn our eyes back to God and restore common sense.https://t.co/gfVOV29fY0  - Katie Britt (@KatieBrittforAL)July 26, 2024        Sen. Brittcalled onpresumptive Democratic Presidential nominee Kamala Harris to condemn the grotesque imitation and the message it sent to audiences.\\u00a0\\\"America is at a crossroads. There are two very different paths. Craziness vs. common sense,\\\" Britt said. \\\"We all know which road the most liberal presidential nominee in history would drive us down.\\\"  Wife of President Joe Biden, First Lady Jill Biden, who led the U.S. delegation to the Olympics this year,saidthe ceremony was \\\"spectacular.\\\"  \\\"Every step of the way, I was thinking to myself, oh my god, oh my god,\\\" Biden said. \\\"How are we going to top this?\\\"  Michael Brauner is a Senior Sports Analyst and Contributing Writer for Yellowhammer News. You can follow him on Twitter@MBraunerWNSPand hear him every weekday morning from 6 to 9 a.m. on\\\"The\\u00a0Opening Kickoff\\\" on WNSP-FM 105.5,available free online.  Jim Zeigler-4 hours ago  Yaffee-6 hours ago  Sherri Blevins-4 days ago  Bibby Bailey-2 weeks ago  Grayson Everett-2 weeks ago  Grayson Everett-3 weeks ago  Grayson Everett-4 weeks ago  Sherri Blevins-4 weeks ago  Next Post  Yellowhammer News is Alabama's preeminent outlet for news, analysis and much more. We are committed to delivering the news in a manner that reflects the state of Alabama, its people and their values.  Privacy Policy  Corrections Policy  Fact Checking Policy  Ownership  Contact Editors  Advertising  \\u00a9 2025 Yellowhammer News\"}"